1.0beta2 - [RELEASEDATE]

- Added convenience method ezcConsoleOutput::outputLine(). This one adds a
  line break after outputting the desired text and works also without any
  text to print a blank line (similar to Pascals writeln()).
- Added option filter parameter to eczConsoleParameter::getHelp().
- Added a new class ezcConsoleOption to represent a single option (This was a
  named parameter before and used an array for the structure).
- Added ia new setting "mandatory" to ezcConsoleOption to indicate that an 
  option has always to be submitted.
- Added cell, row and table based format and alignment settings to
  ezcConsoleTable.
- Added real inheritence of format and alignment through ezcConsoleTable. 
- Added <borderFormat> property to rows to set a specific format for use when
  printing the row border.

- Refactored the whole package to fit into the unified layout and provide a
  much more convenient API.
- Changed to the use of structs instead of complex array structures for
  ezcConsoleOptionRule, ezcConsoleOutputFormat, ezcConsoleOutputFormats,
  ezcConsoleOutputOptions, ezcConsoleProgressbarOptions and
  eczConsoleTableOptions.
- Changed the handling of parameter names in ezcConsoleInput. Short and long
  parameters are now handled equally without their prefix everywhere.
- Changed all classes to use overloading property access - __get(), __set(),
  __isset() - where possible (more convenient API).
- Changed the handling of default values for ezcComponentOption.
- Changed the handling of table structure to classes ezcConsoleTableRow and
  ezcConsoleTableCell.  These allow a convenient way
  to create and customize console based tables:
  * "$table[0][];" creates a new cell
  * "$table[2][]->format = 'important';" creates a new cell and set's it's
    format to 'important'
  * "$table[2]->align = ezcConsoleTable::ALIGN_CENTER;" set's the default
    alignment for the 2nd row to "ALIGN_CENTER".

- Renamed ezcConsoleParameter to ezcConsoleInput. Options are now handled
  through the ezcConsoleOption class.
- Renamed methods:
  * ezcConsoleOutput::styleText() to ezcConsoleOutput::formatText()
  * ezcConsoleInput::fromString() to ezcConsoleInput::registerOptionString()

- Fixed bug with argument handling and non-value parameters in ezcConsoleInput.
- Fixed bug with submitting multiple parameters of the same name without value
  in ezcConsoleInput.


1.0beta1 - Friday 25 November 2005

- Initial release of this package.
